      "writtenOn": "2018-08-01T21:33:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not trying to count errors, I\u0027m trying to figure out when the majority of instructions are received/acknowledged to see if a spike in VMs receiving and then acking an instruction is related to an increase in latency. All I see with the HTTP request instrumentation is that sometimes a request to MP takes awhile.\n\nSpeaking of HTTP request instrumentation, this already acts as a proxy for poll call monitoring. You can tell the agent is alive by the fact that it is still sending HTTP requests to Machine Provider.\n\nError monitoring would probably be good, I didn\u0027t include all the metrics I could think of in this CL in case something was fundamentally wrong with the way I\u0027m reporting them. I was considering adding a metric for time between receipt and ack as well.",
      "parentUuid": "320a49c0_08bde38f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 317,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 317,
        "endChar": 22
      },
      "revId": "d3667191d6c09320c8c79ad49cd954a14a350f9b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "dc680160_4712e9af",
        "filename": "mp/cmd/mpagent/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 317,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-08-01T22:20:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Increase in what latency?\n\nTracking both number of received instructions and number of acked instructions still seems pointless to me. The most you can do is to take a difference of them, and it will give some vague number of \"number of errored instructions since the beginning of times + number of currently running instructions\". It is not very useful number IMHO.\n\nIf you are tracking latency of \u0027configureSwarmingAutoStart + ack\u0027, just measure it directly and send as cumulative distribution.\n\nIf you track only spikes in instruction processing, either one of \u0027instructionsReceived\u0027 or \u0027instructionsAcked\u0027 will do (assuming error rates are negligible). If they are not negligible, I still think it is better to track instructionsReceived + number of errors.\n\nPlease describe how are you going to use the metrics, maybe I just misunderstand.",
      "parentUuid": "93950f04_280d84f5",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 317,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 317,
        "endChar": 22
      },
      "revId": "d3667191d6c09320c8c79ad49cd954a14a350f9b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d254465f_21fa7921",
        "filename": "mp/cmd/mpagent/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 317,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-08-01T22:30:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The latency I\u0027m observing is in HTTP request duration. If I understand the default metrics correctly, the time between sending an HTTP request and receiving a response. Sometimes it takes a long time to get a response from Machine Provider.\n\nI\u0027m not trying to take a difference between acks and receipts, that wouldn\u0027t really make sense. I guess I\u0027m using ts_mon here as event_mon, I\u0027m trying to report a count of \"something interesting happened\" to see if lots of \"interesting thing happened\" events correlate with anything else.\n\nI am not tracking latency in this CL, I meant I am considering tracking latency in a cumulative later on if the overall approach in this CL (% the particular metrics) is correct.\n\nHow I intend to use them is just as a signal that stuff is occurring, similar to MP\u0027s serverside metrics (e.g. lease_requests_fulfilled++). I don\u0027t expect to design alerts based on these metrics.",
